## ðŸ§  Key Concepts Learned

- **Threat Hunting** is a proactive approach to identifying threats that may have evaded traditional security tools.
- **Threat Hunting Methodologies**:
  - Hypothesis-Driven
  - Intelligence-Driven
  - Analytics-Driven

## ðŸ§± MITRE ATT&CK Framework

- A structured knowledge base of adversary tactics and techniques.
- Helps map incidents to known behavior patterns for faster and smarter detection.

### Tactics vs. Techniques

| Tactic               | Example Technique                        |
|----------------------|------------------------------------------|
| Initial Access        | Phishing (T1566)                        |
| Execution             | Command & Scripting Interpreter (T1059) |

